description: Recently sold: $258,000. 3319 75th St. E., Inver Grove Heights This delightful 3 Bedroom, 1.75 Bath rambler in Inver Grove Heights is just the home you've been waiting for! A lovely neighborhood with wonderful neighbors! With many updates throughout while also retaining original charm, you will plenty of storage and living space for you and your family. Inside, you will find original hardwood floors, a large bay window, and built in oak cabinetry in the front room, currently used as a dining room. The kitchen has newer appliances, including a gas range with both a traditional and a convection oven. To the rear of the home, a living room off the kitchen leads to a large cedar deck. This light filled room includes a new window and new oversized sliding door to the deck. Three bright and spacious bedrooms are all on the main level. The large bathroom features plaster walls, double vanity, new tub surround (with a transferrable warranty) and glass shower door. New mold resistant wall board was installed behind the surround, as well. The lower level is finished with a family room and plenty of space for a home theater, gaming table, home office and hobbies or playroom. You will also find a large storage room with a cedar closet as well as a ¾ bath and the laundry room. Updates include new mold resistant green board, paneling, drop ceiling, recessed lights, new doors and carpet. Outdoors, the large back yard is private and fenced. Mature trees of different varieties provide shade on the 13ftx27ft cedar deck. Beautiful retaining walls and paver front walk/steps were professionally installed and add a touch of elegance to the easy care landscape. The front yard has an automatic sprinkler system. Both the home and garage have gutters, with gutter guards on the garage and rear of the home. The real gem of this home is the oversized 3 car heated and insulated garage. A rare find, this 30ft.x30ft garage provides plenty of room to store your vehicles and toys as well as a workbench. A ceiling fan circulates the heated air making this a very comfortable space to work in the winter. With the basketball hoop, the large concrete driveway is a great place to practice your jump shot! Updated mechanicals include a new forced air furnace, April Aire humidifier, Honeywell air filter (all 2006) and Culligan water softener in 2011. The water heater was replaced in 2004. The large back yard is private and fenced. Mature trees of different varieties provide shade on the 13ftx27ft cedar deck. Presented by John and Becky Durham, top selling RE/MAX Results real estate agents with the Durham Executive Group in Woodbury, MN. We are accredited relocation agents specializing in the luxury home market, but are proud to serve clients in all price points and stages of life, from first time home buyers to down-sizing empty nesters. For more information about our executive level real estate services in the Twin Cities and Western Wisconsin, check out our website at www.DurhamExecutiveGroup.com.

description:
Recently sold: $212,000. Feel the warmth as you enter this beautifully spacious townhome.  From the tones on the walls to the custom built fireplace mantle made of handpicked natural stone and oak.  On the first floor, the high ceilings, open floor plan, laminate flooring and abundant windows contribute to a very spacious and comfortable environment.  The living room and dining room lead into the kitchen.  The black whirpool appliances and Stainless Steel Sink lends a modern feel to the kitchen.  There is also a built-in island which makes a great coffee bar.  A powder room and closet complete the lower floor.  Up the stairs we find the bedrooms.  There are two bedrooms, one is a huge Master suite (13x10) with a walk in closet.  The other is slightly smaller and could also be adapted to be an office or a craft room.  The third space is the loft area.  This would make the perfect reading nook, exercise area or whatever your heart desires.  It could even be converted into a third bedroom should the need arise.  On the other side of the hallway we have the laundry room with full size washer and dryer, a linen closet and the upstairs bathroom.  This is a large bathroom with a full bath and a built in double sink vanity.  The spacious garage area has plenty of room for two cars and has a small driveway out to the street.  The patio/deck on the front of the building will allow you to sip tea on those summer nights and enjoy the view of the park like area adjacent to the home.  Located only 10 minutes from the mall of america and MSP airport, it is a very convenient location.  $1450/mo, $45 application fee

Owner pays for Association Fee, Water, Trash, Lawn Care and Snow Removal
